# Next.js 15 App Router Patterns

## App Router Structure
- Use `app/` directory for all routes
- Implement proper layouts with [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx)
- Use route groups for organization
- Implement loading and error boundaries

## Server Components (Default)
- Use Server Components by default
- Access database directly in Server Components
- Use async/await for data fetching
- Implement proper error handling

## Client Components
- Add `"use client"` directive when needed
- Use for interactive features
- Implement proper state management
- Use React hooks appropriately

## Data Fetching
- Use Server Actions for mutations
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use Next.js built-in caching
- Handle loading and error states